## Artifacts (CC BY 4.0)

Data and result artifacts in this repository are licensed under Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0), matching the companion paper.
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

This covers the files under:

  stage_b/data/                  stage_b/profiles/
  stage_b/data_bench/            stage_b/profiles_bench/
  stage_b/profiles_ext/          stage_b/profiles_ext_gemma4/
  modal/data_upload/             modal/refs_upload/

and the *.json result files at any level.

## Third-party code vendored in this repository

  vendor/t0_core/    minimal extraction import closure from t0-morphology-furnace
  modal/seal/        the seal modules mounted by the GPU extractor, vendored verbatim
                     at the versions that actually ran (see modal/PROVENANCE.md)

Both are (c) 2026 Michael S. R. Kitti and carried under the MIT terms above.

## Upstream datasets

The evaluation prompts derive from the datasets below, which retain their original
licenses. Redistribution here is for reproducibility of the registered analyses.

  ANLI       Nie et al., 2020. Adversarial NLI: A New Benchmark for Natural
             Language Understanding. ACL 2020. CC BY-NC 4.0.
             https://github.com/facebookresearch/anli

  TriviaQA   Joshi et al., 2017. TriviaQA: A Large Scale Distantly Supervised
             Challenge Dataset for Reading Comprehension. ACL 2017. Apache-2.0.
             https://github.com/mandarjoshi90/triviaqa

  HaluEval   Li et al., 2023. HaluEval: A Large-Scale Hallucination Evaluation
             Benchmark for Large Language Models. EMNLP 2023. MIT License.
             https://github.com/RUCAIBox/HaluEval
             Used by the BENCH extension (stage_b/data_bench/). The HaluEval MIT
             notice is reproduced below as required by that license.

